begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation, we introduced ourselves and where we're from. We laughed about Idaho and Ohio being confused with each other! We also talked about what we currently do for work.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we talked about our families and especially how we both share our birthdays with family members, which was another interesting thing we have in common.
end_memory_text: We talked more about his family and religion, especially Mormonism and Catholicism. We also talked about where we went to college and then our interests in sports, especially professional baseball.
rest_of_day_open: I'm excited for this weekend! I'm going to take a break from doing a lot of studying tonight and lay in bed with my cat and maybe watch a movie. Tomorrow, I'm doing a new volunteer opportunity that I'm really excited about and then I get to watch my favorite team play football!
critical_positive: The conversation worked well because we had a lot of common! We were also very respectful of each other and gave each other full room to talk, even if we had a comment to make in response. I think that we both approached the conversation with an open mind, which helped make it go so well.
critical_negative: I think our conversation worked really well, so this is hard to come up with answers for. begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves, and found out where each other was from. We then joked about how we both live in parts of the country that are often forgotten by the rest of the states! We also talked about what each other did for a living.
middle_memory_text: We discussed some of the things we had in common that we didn't know we had in common. For example, both of us were born on our father's birthday, and both of our fathers were in the Air Force. After that we talked about her career path to become a doctor and why she wanted to do that.
end_memory_text: Towards the end of the conversation I asked her about her sweatshirt because she was wearing a Notre Dame sweatshirt. She said she absolutely loved Notre Dame because that is where she went to school. We also talked about how I was not super close to my family because of all the difference is that I have from the rest of my family. We then talked about Mormonism and Catholicism for a while because she grew up Catholic and I grew up Mormon. Finally, we ended the conversation discussing sports, and in particular, baseball and why the World Series is called the World Series.
rest_of_day_open: I don't imagine the rest of my week will be too eventful. I've already had my main appointment that I have every week, and I've done grocery shopping as well. I stay home a lot more because of the coronavirus, and I imagine that will be what I do for the rest of this weekend pretty much.
critical_positive: The conversation had a super awesome flow to it. We were laughing and joking and having a good time, as well as discovering that we had some things in common which made the conversation move quickly and flow naturally. To be honest, I was disappointed when the conversation was over.
critical_negative: I think I was at fault for what did not go well during the conversation. I was talking a lot and didn't ask as many questions as I would've liked. Sometimes, she would ask me a question and I would not return the same question to her to find out her answers. That is something I would have liked to do better.
